<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="127" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" status="stat. rev." subSpecies="aurargentea">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</taxonomicName>
Mazel, 1979, Entomops, Nice 6: 267, figs 1, 2 (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. rev.">Zygaena</taxonomicName>
). Type-locality. France: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pyrénées-Orientales">Pyrenees-Orientales</normalizedToken>
, Coustouges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="4" pageNumber="127" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="127">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="4" pageNumber="127">
Described from Coustouges (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pyrénées-Orientales">Pyrenees-Orientales</normalizedToken>
, France), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">
<pageBreakToken pageId="5" pageNumber="128" start="start">Zygaena</pageBreakToken>
rhadamanthus aurargentea
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also found in Spain (Barcelona and Gerona, excluding coastal regions). It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="rhadamanthus" authorityName="rhadamanthus (Esper" authorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="rhadamanthus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus rhadamanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the extreme griseoid phenotype, i.e. with pronounced white scaling on the ground colour of the forewings, especially in the females, which is reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthuer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from south-eastern and southern-central France (see above), and by the presence of a strong abdominal cingulum that is also present ventrally. 
<bibRefCitation author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98) placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which he reinstated as a valid subspecies, but we see no justification for this (see also above). The former is here reinstated (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">stat. rev.</emphasis>
) as a valid subspecies, based on its extreme phenotype, which is so strongly different from that of the nominotypical taxon 
<taxonomicName authority="rhadamanthus" authorityName="rhadamanthus (Esper" authorityYear="1789" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. rhadamanthus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="rhadamanthus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus rhadamanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B17" refString="Hofmann, A, Tremewan, WG, 1996. A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae). Harley Books, Colchester" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan 1996</bibRefCitation>
: 131).
</paragraph>
